<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Remarks</h4>
	<div class="text"> <i>Muhlenbergia rigens </i>is a large perennial bunchgrass that forms tussocks up to 2 m tall. It occurs in California and from southern Nevada to Texas. It is associated with moist environments in arid or Mediterranean climates. <br/>
<br/>
Stands are typically small and widely scattered. They occur in settings with periodic disturbance, and stands can withstand periodic f looding and burning. Ecologically, they are typically less moist than <i>Juncus</i>- or <i>Carex</i>-dominated meadows, but more mesic than most other grasslands away from the immediate coast of California. The largest inventoried are approximately 0.5 ha. </div>
</div>

    
	
	
