<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Fire Characteristics</h4>
	<div class="text"><i>Muhlenbergia rigens </i>increases greatly in productivity after most fires by rapid growth from the basal buds and seedling establishment. In addition, dead material is cleared away, and nutrients are recycled (Anderson 2005). 

In San Diego Co., <i>M. rigens </i>regained 51% to 145% more live foliage within 3-15 months after prescribed burns than did unburned controls, and over three times more <i>M. rigens </i>clumps in one burn area than in the control. It appeared that f lower and seed production increased and plants recovered better after spring burning than after late fall burning (Fryer 2007).</div>
	<table class="zebraStripe">
		
		<tr>
			<td class="key">Fire return interval</td>
			<td>Short
				
